		//Title: The white text at the top of the help menu.
		"title"			"Welcome to Chaos Fortress! What would you like to know?"
		
		//Button Name: This button will be displayed in the menu as "What is Chaos Fortress?"
		"What is this?"
		{
			//Messages: A number of chat messages, which will be printed to the user's chat when the button is pressed.
			"1"		"{unusual}Chaos Fortress{default} is a community game mode, which takes {orange}Team Fortress 2{default}'s core gameplay and modifies it by introducing {green}custom characters{default}."
			"2"		"Each character has access to their own unique set of weapons and abilities, including a powerful {haunted}Ultimate Ability{default}, activated by calling for medic upon reaching 100%%."
		}
		
		"How do I change my class/choose my character?"
		{
			"1"		"You can choose your character by typing {yellow}/c{default} in chat. This opens up a menu, displaying all of the characters, as well as their roles."
			"2"		"Pressing a character's button will open a sub-menu, displaying that character's name, the TF2 class they are most similar to, and a brief description of their gameplay."
			"3"		"Here, you may choose to spawn as that character, or read a more detailed description of their gameplay. There's also an option to read a bit about their lore, if you're into that sort of thing."
			"4"		"Note that each character is limited to {yellow}3{default} per team, or {yellow}2{default} for characters of the {vintage}Tank{default} role."
		}
		
		"How do I use abilities?"
		{
			"1"		"Each character has up to 4 types of abilities: an {haunted}Ultimate Ability{default}, an {haunted}M2{default} ability, a {haunted}Spec. Attack{default} ability, and a {haunted}Reload{default} ability."
			"2"		"{haunted}M2{default} abilities are activated by clicking your {yellow}alt-fire (+attack2){default} bind, which is {yellow}right-click by default{default}."
			"3"		"{haunted}Spec. Attack{default} abilities are activated by clicking your {yellow}special attack (+attack3){default} bind, which is {yellow}middle mouse by default."
			"4"		"{haunted}Reload{default} abilities are activated by pressing your {yellow}reload (+reload){default} bind, which is {yellow}R by default{default}."
			"5"		"{haunted}Ultimate Abilities{default} are activated, once fully-charged, by {yellow}calling for medic (voicemenu 0 0){default}, which is {yellow}E by default{default}."
		}
		
		"Extra Ability Info"
		{
			"1"		"Some characters have {yellow}held{default} abilities. These are abilities which provide their effects while their respective key is held, such as Mercenary's Sprint ability providing a speed boost while holding M2."
			"2"		"Additionally, some characters use a special resource for their abilities, such as Orbital Sniper's Fuel. Abilities with a resource cost cannot be used unless you have enough of the required resource."
			"3"		"If your character uses resources, your {yellow}current resources{default} are displayed above your abilities, directly below your {haunted}Ultimate Ability{default}. The resource cost of each ability is displayed in brackets to the right of the ability."
		}
		
		"How do I make a suggestion/report a bug?"
		{
			"1"		"All suggestions and bug reports are submitted via our {unusual}Discord{default} server, which can be joined here: {green}discord.gg/bobschaosagency{default}. We pay very close attention to all reports and suggestions submitted here."
			"2"		"You may encounter a developer while playing. In these cases, we ask that you please {crimson}do not{default} report bugs/make suggestions directly to them. If you do this, you will be ignored."
		}
		
		"Is there anything else I should know?"
		{
			"1"		"You can tell your team via text chat what your current {haunted}Ultimate Ability{default} charge is by using the ''Activate Charge!'' voice command (console bind: voicemenu 1 6)."
			"2"		"Random crits are {red}disabled{default} in this game mode. However, {yellow}certain abilities still use crit particles and sound effects{default} as visual/audio indicators."
		}
	}
		
